{"id":759,"date":"2022-01-15T12:16:48","date_gmt":"2022-01-15T12:16:48","guid":{"rendered":"https:\/\/thetechcorner.org\/?p=759"},"modified":"2022-01-15T12:16:55","modified_gmt":"2022-01-15T12:16:55","slug":"conditionally-execute-code-use-of-if-test-etc","status":"publish","type":"post","link":"https:\/\/thetechcorner.org\/?p=759","title":{"rendered":"Conditionally execute code (use of: if, test, [], etc.)"},"content":{"rendered":"\n<h3>Hello World Bash Shell Script<\/h3>\n\n\n\n<p><strong>The first, <\/strong>most basic script everyone who has ever scripted done was the &#8220;<strong>Hello World<\/strong>&#8220;. The whole purpose is to just print this sentence on the terminal using &#8220;echo&#8221; command.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>Simply use any text editor of your choice and type in the following code:<\/p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-full is-style-default\"><img decoding=\"async\" loading=\"lazy\" width=\"640\" height=\"106\" src=\"https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/thetechcorner.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/01\/image-80.png?resize=640%2C106&#038;ssl=1\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-763\" srcset=\"https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/thetechcorner.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/01\/image-80.png?w=806&amp;ssl=1 806w, https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/thetechcorner.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/01\/image-80.png?resize=300%2C50&amp;ssl=1 300w, https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/thetechcorner.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/01\/image-80.png?resize=768%2C127&amp;ssl=1 768w, https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/thetechcorner.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/01\/image-80.png?resize=24%2C4&amp;ssl=1 24w, https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/thetechcorner.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/01\/image-80.png?resize=36%2C6&amp;ssl=1 36w, https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/thetechcorner.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/01\/image-80.png?resize=48%2C8&amp;ssl=1 48w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 640px) 100vw, 640px\" data-recalc-dims=\"1\" \/><\/figure>\n\n\n\n<p><\/p>\n\n\n\n<p><strong>Once you have it, save the file and add execute permission<\/strong> to the script because without it Linux would refuse to execute the script as the permission name suggests. We do it with the following command<\/p>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"is-layout-flow wp-block-group\"><div class=\"wp-block-group__inner-container\">\n<pre class=\"wp-block-preformatted\">chmod +x hello_world.sh<\/pre>\n<\/div><\/div>\n\n\n\n<p>And simple start the script with the<\/p>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"is-layout-flow wp-block-group\"><div class=\"wp-block-group__inner-container\">\n<pre class=\"wp-block-preformatted\">.\/hello_world<\/pre>\n<\/div><\/div>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-full is-style-default\"><img decoding=\"async\" loading=\"lazy\" width=\"560\" height=\"104\" src=\"https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/thetechcorner.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/01\/image-81.png?resize=560%2C104&#038;ssl=1\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-764\" srcset=\"https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/thetechcorner.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/01\/image-81.png?w=560&amp;ssl=1 560w, https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/thetechcorner.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/01\/image-81.png?resize=300%2C56&amp;ssl=1 300w, https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/thetechcorner.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/01\/image-81.png?resize=24%2C4&amp;ssl=1 24w, https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/thetechcorner.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/01\/image-81.png?resize=36%2C7&amp;ssl=1 36w, https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/thetechcorner.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/01\/image-81.png?resize=48%2C9&amp;ssl=1 48w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 560px) 100vw, 560px\" data-recalc-dims=\"1\" \/><\/figure>\n\n\n\n<p><\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>You may have noticed few things, starting out with the weird first line in our text file. &#8220;<strong>#!\/bin\/bash<\/strong>&#8221; or so-called <strong>shebang<\/strong> is a way to define your script\u2019s interpreter as\u00a0Bash. We first locate a full path to its executable binary using\u00a0<code>which<\/code>\u00a0command, prefix it with a shebang <code>#!<\/code>\u00a0and insert it as the first line of your script.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>Another small detail is the way we named our script. It&#8217;s not really about coming up with the good name, but all bash shell scripts should end with the extension &#8220;<strong>.sh<\/strong>&#8220;. It&#8217;s not necessary for the script to work, Linux doesn&#8217;t need a kind of file naming system it&#8217;s just the convection we Linux administrator do, to tell files apart. <\/p>\n\n\n\n<p><\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>With this basis information, we can finally move to this lesson topics.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p><\/p>\n\n\n\n<h3><strong>Returning the exit codes<\/strong><\/h3>\n\n\n\n<p>To understand how If and [] and everything else in bash scripting works, we need to know about the exit codes.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>The most basic principle in the shell programming is: If something is true it&#8217;s 0 and if it&#8217;s anything else it&#8217;s not 0. Maybe it sounds confusing, but let me explain.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>If we started with the blank shell terminal, and we would type &#8220;echo $?&#8221; we would get &#8220;0&#8221;<\/p>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-image is-style-default\"><figure class=\"aligncenter size-full\"><img decoding=\"async\" loading=\"lazy\" width=\"467\" height=\"67\" src=\"https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/thetechcorner.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/01\/image-82.png?resize=467%2C67&#038;ssl=1\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-765\" srcset=\"https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/thetechcorner.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/01\/image-82.png?w=467&amp;ssl=1 467w, https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/thetechcorner.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/01\/image-82.png?resize=300%2C43&amp;ssl=1 300w, https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/thetechcorner.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/01\/image-82.png?resize=24%2C3&amp;ssl=1 24w, https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/thetechcorner.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/01\/image-82.png?resize=36%2C5&amp;ssl=1 36w, https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/thetechcorner.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/01\/image-82.png?resize=48%2C7&amp;ssl=1 48w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 467px) 100vw, 467px\" data-recalc-dims=\"1\" \/><\/figure><\/div>\n\n\n\n<p>Because we didn&#8217;t previously enter code that would issue exit code false, its default is the true. Let&#8217;s try to use the wrong command.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-image is-style-default\"><figure class=\"aligncenter size-full\"><img decoding=\"async\" loading=\"lazy\" width=\"515\" height=\"101\" src=\"https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/thetechcorner.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/01\/image-83.png?resize=515%2C101&#038;ssl=1\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-766\" srcset=\"https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/thetechcorner.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/01\/image-83.png?w=515&amp;ssl=1 515w, https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/thetechcorner.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/01\/image-83.png?resize=300%2C59&amp;ssl=1 300w, https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/thetechcorner.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/01\/image-83.png?resize=24%2C5&amp;ssl=1 24w, https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/thetechcorner.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/01\/image-83.png?resize=36%2C7&amp;ssl=1 36w, https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/thetechcorner.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/01\/image-83.png?resize=48%2C9&amp;ssl=1 48w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 515px) 100vw, 515px\" data-recalc-dims=\"1\" \/><\/figure><\/div>\n\n\n\n<p>Let&#8217;s try another example with the real command this time<\/p>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-image is-style-default\"><figure class=\"aligncenter size-full is-resized\"><img decoding=\"async\" loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/thetechcorner.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/01\/image-84.png?resize=453%2C207&#038;ssl=1\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-767\" width=\"453\" height=\"207\" srcset=\"https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/thetechcorner.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/01\/image-84.png?w=453&amp;ssl=1 453w, https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/thetechcorner.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/01\/image-84.png?resize=300%2C137&amp;ssl=1 300w, https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/thetechcorner.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/01\/image-84.png?resize=24%2C11&amp;ssl=1 24w, https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/thetechcorner.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/01\/image-84.png?resize=36%2C16&amp;ssl=1 36w, https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/thetechcorner.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/01\/image-84.png?resize=48%2C22&amp;ssl=1 48w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 453px) 100vw, 453px\" data-recalc-dims=\"1\" \/><\/figure><\/div>\n\n\n\n<p><\/p>\n\n\n\n<p><strong>Ok, so I hope now you get the point of what I&#8217;m trying to say. Whenever the command we issue it&#8217;s correct it returns an exit code of 0 and whenever for some reason it&#8217;s not the exit code changes.<\/strong><\/p>\n\n\n\n<p><\/p>\n\n\n\n<h3>Equality operators<\/h3>\n\n\n\n<p>That brings us to more complex statements, which are equality operators { ==  &lt; >  }<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>I&#8217;ll demonstrate this once again on the example first to get the point<\/p>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-image is-style-default\"><figure class=\"aligncenter size-full\"><img decoding=\"async\" loading=\"lazy\" width=\"367\" height=\"224\" src=\"https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/thetechcorner.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/01\/image-86.png?resize=367%2C224&#038;ssl=1\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-769\" srcset=\"https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/thetechcorner.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/01\/image-86.png?w=367&amp;ssl=1 367w, https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/thetechcorner.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/01\/image-86.png?resize=300%2C183&amp;ssl=1 300w, https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/thetechcorner.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/01\/image-86.png?resize=24%2C15&amp;ssl=1 24w, https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/thetechcorner.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/01\/image-86.png?resize=36%2C22&amp;ssl=1 36w, https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/thetechcorner.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/01\/image-86.png?resize=48%2C29&amp;ssl=1 48w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 367px) 100vw, 367px\" data-recalc-dims=\"1\" \/><\/figure><\/div>\n\n\n\n<p>Let&#8217;s ignore the if loop first, I&#8217;ll explain that later. First, look at the logic behind this script. If &#8220;bla&#8221; equals &#8220;bla&#8221; the if loop will exit with the exit code 0 which means we will see It&#8217;s true statement in the terminal.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-image is-style-default\"><figure class=\"aligncenter size-full\"><img decoding=\"async\" loading=\"lazy\" width=\"396\" height=\"61\" src=\"https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/thetechcorner.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/01\/image-87.png?resize=396%2C61&#038;ssl=1\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-770\" srcset=\"https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/thetechcorner.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/01\/image-87.png?w=396&amp;ssl=1 396w, https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/thetechcorner.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/01\/image-87.png?resize=300%2C46&amp;ssl=1 300w, https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/thetechcorner.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/01\/image-87.png?resize=24%2C4&amp;ssl=1 24w, https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/thetechcorner.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/01\/image-87.png?resize=36%2C6&amp;ssl=1 36w, https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/thetechcorner.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/01\/image-87.png?resize=48%2C7&amp;ssl=1 48w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 396px) 100vw, 396px\" data-recalc-dims=\"1\" \/><\/figure><\/div>\n\n\n\n<p><\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>Another operators are self-explanatory as well with some basic math skills<\/p>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-image is-style-default\"><figure class=\"aligncenter size-full\"><img decoding=\"async\" loading=\"lazy\" width=\"640\" height=\"338\" src=\"https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/thetechcorner.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/01\/image-88.png?resize=640%2C338&#038;ssl=1\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-771\" srcset=\"https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/thetechcorner.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/01\/image-88.png?w=688&amp;ssl=1 688w, https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/thetechcorner.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/01\/image-88.png?resize=300%2C158&amp;ssl=1 300w, https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/thetechcorner.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/01\/image-88.png?resize=24%2C13&amp;ssl=1 24w, https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/thetechcorner.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/01\/image-88.png?resize=36%2C19&amp;ssl=1 36w, https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/thetechcorner.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/01\/image-88.png?resize=48%2C25&amp;ssl=1 48w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 640px) 100vw, 640px\" data-recalc-dims=\"1\" \/><\/figure><\/div>\n\n\n\n<p>In the bash, we can also type out these operators with the shortcuts of their meaning, here is a table<\/p>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-image is-style-default\"><figure class=\"aligncenter size-full\"><img decoding=\"async\" loading=\"lazy\" width=\"623\" height=\"293\" src=\"https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/thetechcorner.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/01\/image-92.png?resize=623%2C293&#038;ssl=1\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-775\" srcset=\"https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/thetechcorner.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/01\/image-92.png?w=623&amp;ssl=1 623w, https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/thetechcorner.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/01\/image-92.png?resize=300%2C141&amp;ssl=1 300w, https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/thetechcorner.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/01\/image-92.png?resize=24%2C11&amp;ssl=1 24w, https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/thetechcorner.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/01\/image-92.png?resize=36%2C17&amp;ssl=1 36w, https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/thetechcorner.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/01\/image-92.png?resize=48%2C23&amp;ssl=1 48w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 623px) 100vw, 623px\" data-recalc-dims=\"1\" \/><\/figure><\/div>\n\n\n\n<p><\/p>\n\n\n\n<h2>Logical operators <\/h2>\n\n\n\n<p>Now we can proceed with some work with logical operations. These logical or so called boolean operators are used to compare values and decide on what to do next with the result. <\/p>\n\n\n\n<p><\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>Here are the tables explaining all the possibilities<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p><strong>AND<\/strong> <strong>&amp;&amp;<\/strong><\/p>\n\n\n\n<p><\/p>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-image is-style-default\"><figure class=\"aligncenter size-full\"><img decoding=\"async\" loading=\"lazy\" width=\"189\" height=\"168\" src=\"https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/thetechcorner.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/01\/image-95.png?resize=189%2C168&#038;ssl=1\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-779\" srcset=\"https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/thetechcorner.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/01\/image-95.png?w=189&amp;ssl=1 189w, https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/thetechcorner.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/01\/image-95.png?resize=24%2C21&amp;ssl=1 24w, https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/thetechcorner.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/01\/image-95.png?resize=36%2C32&amp;ssl=1 36w, https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/thetechcorner.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/01\/image-95.png?resize=48%2C43&amp;ssl=1 48w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 189px) 100vw, 189px\" data-recalc-dims=\"1\" \/><\/figure><\/div>\n\n\n\n<p class=\"has-text-align-center\"><strong> <\/strong><\/p>\n\n\n\n<p><strong>OR ||<\/strong><\/p>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-image is-style-default\"><figure class=\"aligncenter size-full\"><img decoding=\"async\" loading=\"lazy\" width=\"181\" height=\"195\" src=\"https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/thetechcorner.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/01\/image-96.png?resize=181%2C195&#038;ssl=1\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-780\" srcset=\"https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/thetechcorner.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/01\/image-96.png?w=181&amp;ssl=1 181w, https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/thetechcorner.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/01\/image-96.png?resize=22%2C24&amp;ssl=1 22w, https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/thetechcorner.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/01\/image-96.png?resize=33%2C36&amp;ssl=1 33w, https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/thetechcorner.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/01\/image-96.png?resize=45%2C48&amp;ssl=1 45w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 181px) 100vw, 181px\" data-recalc-dims=\"1\" \/><\/figure><\/div>\n\n\n\n<p><\/p>\n\n\n\n<p><strong>NOT !=<\/strong><\/p>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-image is-style-default\"><figure class=\"aligncenter size-full\"><img decoding=\"async\" loading=\"lazy\" width=\"178\" height=\"150\" src=\"https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/thetechcorner.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/01\/image-97.png?resize=178%2C150&#038;ssl=1\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-781\" srcset=\"https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/thetechcorner.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/01\/image-97.png?w=178&amp;ssl=1 178w, https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/thetechcorner.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/01\/image-97.png?resize=24%2C20&amp;ssl=1 24w, https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/thetechcorner.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/01\/image-97.png?resize=36%2C30&amp;ssl=1 36w, https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/thetechcorner.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/01\/image-97.png?resize=48%2C40&amp;ssl=1 48w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 178px) 100vw, 178px\" data-recalc-dims=\"1\" \/><\/figure><\/div>\n\n\n\n<p><\/p>\n\n\n\n<p><\/p>\n\n\n\n<h3>test command []<\/h3>\n\n\n\n<p>To find out more about this command, let&#8217;s type <strong>man test<\/strong> to get more info.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-image is-style-default\"><figure class=\"aligncenter size-full\"><img decoding=\"async\" loading=\"lazy\" width=\"640\" height=\"232\" src=\"https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/thetechcorner.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/01\/image-89.png?resize=640%2C232&#038;ssl=1\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-772\" srcset=\"https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/thetechcorner.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/01\/image-89.png?w=704&amp;ssl=1 704w, https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/thetechcorner.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/01\/image-89.png?resize=300%2C109&amp;ssl=1 300w, https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/thetechcorner.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/01\/image-89.png?resize=24%2C9&amp;ssl=1 24w, https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/thetechcorner.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/01\/image-89.png?resize=36%2C13&amp;ssl=1 36w, https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/thetechcorner.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/01\/image-89.png?resize=48%2C17&amp;ssl=1 48w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 640px) 100vw, 640px\" data-recalc-dims=\"1\" \/><\/figure><\/div>\n\n\n\n<p>If you still don&#8217;t understand, don&#8217;t worry, let me elaborate. <\/p>\n\n\n\n<p><strong>The test<\/strong> <strong>command is a quick little tool which allow us to test the statements<\/strong>. This comes very handy as we don&#8217;t need to make scripts files for everything.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-image is-style-default\"><figure class=\"aligncenter size-full\"><img decoding=\"async\" loading=\"lazy\" width=\"533\" height=\"173\" src=\"https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/thetechcorner.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/01\/image-90.png?resize=533%2C173&#038;ssl=1\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-773\" srcset=\"https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/thetechcorner.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/01\/image-90.png?w=533&amp;ssl=1 533w, https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/thetechcorner.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/01\/image-90.png?resize=300%2C97&amp;ssl=1 300w, https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/thetechcorner.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/01\/image-90.png?resize=24%2C8&amp;ssl=1 24w, https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/thetechcorner.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/01\/image-90.png?resize=36%2C12&amp;ssl=1 36w, https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/thetechcorner.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/01\/image-90.png?resize=48%2C16&amp;ssl=1 48w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 533px) 100vw, 533px\" data-recalc-dims=\"1\" \/><\/figure><\/div>\n\n\n\n<p>Let&#8217;s try something a little more complicated with the logical operators. As you can see in the picture below, the script test if number 5 is greater than 2 and if the output is true it will execute the first echo which types out &#8220;true&#8221; and if the expression it not correct it executes the second OR value which is &#8220;false&#8221;.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-image is-style-default\"><figure class=\"aligncenter size-full\"><img decoding=\"async\" loading=\"lazy\" width=\"640\" height=\"137\" src=\"https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/thetechcorner.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/01\/image-91.png?resize=640%2C137&#038;ssl=1\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-774\" srcset=\"https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/thetechcorner.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/01\/image-91.png?w=675&amp;ssl=1 675w, https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/thetechcorner.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/01\/image-91.png?resize=300%2C64&amp;ssl=1 300w, https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/thetechcorner.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/01\/image-91.png?resize=24%2C5&amp;ssl=1 24w, https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/thetechcorner.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/01\/image-91.png?resize=36%2C8&amp;ssl=1 36w, https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/thetechcorner.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/01\/image-91.png?resize=48%2C10&amp;ssl=1 48w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 640px) 100vw, 640px\" data-recalc-dims=\"1\" \/><\/figure><\/div>\n\n\n\n<p><\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>Another way of writing the test command is using the brackets []. According to my knowledge, it&#8217;s just the alias and It doesn&#8217;t matter which one do you use, but I may be wrong.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-image is-style-default\"><figure class=\"aligncenter size-full\"><img decoding=\"async\" loading=\"lazy\" width=\"540\" height=\"105\" src=\"https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/thetechcorner.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/01\/image-98.png?resize=540%2C105&#038;ssl=1\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-782\" srcset=\"https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/thetechcorner.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/01\/image-98.png?w=540&amp;ssl=1 540w, https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/thetechcorner.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/01\/image-98.png?resize=300%2C58&amp;ssl=1 300w, https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/thetechcorner.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/01\/image-98.png?resize=24%2C5&amp;ssl=1 24w, https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/thetechcorner.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/01\/image-98.png?resize=36%2C7&amp;ssl=1 36w, https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/thetechcorner.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/01\/image-98.png?resize=48%2C9&amp;ssl=1 48w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 540px) 100vw, 540px\" data-recalc-dims=\"1\" \/><\/figure><\/div>\n\n\n\n<p><\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>But where this alias comes handy is writing scripts and using the function and the loops. In this lesson, I&#8217;ll show you the first and most common function IF.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p><\/p>\n\n\n\n<h3>IF function<\/h3>\n\n\n\n<p>IF is the first and most common function, as you could probably see in the first script I&#8217;ve showed you<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p><strong>The basic logic behind this function is: IF the first expression is this true do this and if it&#8217;s not do something else.<\/strong><\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>That&#8217;s why the syntax is also written as IF, Else.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-image is-style-default\"><figure class=\"aligncenter size-full\"><img decoding=\"async\" loading=\"lazy\" width=\"308\" height=\"142\" src=\"https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/thetechcorner.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/01\/image-100.png?resize=308%2C142&#038;ssl=1\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-785\" srcset=\"https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/thetechcorner.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/01\/image-100.png?w=308&amp;ssl=1 308w, https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/thetechcorner.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/01\/image-100.png?resize=300%2C138&amp;ssl=1 300w, https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/thetechcorner.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/01\/image-100.png?resize=24%2C11&amp;ssl=1 24w, https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/thetechcorner.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/01\/image-100.png?resize=36%2C17&amp;ssl=1 36w, https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/thetechcorner.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/01\/image-100.png?resize=48%2C22&amp;ssl=1 48w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 308px) 100vw, 308px\" data-recalc-dims=\"1\" \/><\/figure><\/div>\n\n\n\n<p>As you can see, we are using the test [] function inside the IF statement. IF the test function exit with exit code true the IF function executes the first line starting with then. But if the test function exits with exit code false, the IF function proceed with else path.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p><\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>This is all very simplified, but it&#8217;s a good start in understanding the logic behind scripting. I would say it&#8217;s pretty important to just try executing a lot of simple functions to get the point. In the following lessons it&#8217;s going to come a lot more natural, I&#8217;ll promise.<\/p>\n","protected":false},"excerpt":{"rendered":"<p>Hello World Bash Shell Script The first, most basic script everyone who has ever scripted [&hellip;]<\/p>\n","protected":false},"author":1,"featured_media":760,"comment_status":"open","ping_status":"open","sticky":false,"template":"","format":"standard","meta":{"nf_dc_page":"","om_disable_all_campaigns":false,"_mi_skip_tracking":false},"categories":[219],"tags":[284,288,287,285,283,291,289,290,286],"jetpack_featured_media_url":"https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/thetechcorner.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/01\/rhsa-create-simple-shell-scripts-2.png?fit=1280%2C720&ssl=